member.summary:

You can pass second argument that generates new Run overload.
            ConsoleApp.Run(args, (int x, int y) => { });

            ConsoleApp.Run(args, Foo);

            ConsoleApp.Run(args, &Foo);


You can pass second argument that generates new RunAsync overload.
            ConsoleApp.RunAsync(args, (int x, int y) => { });

            ConsoleApp.RunAsync(args, Foo);

            ConsoleApp.RunAsync(args, &Foo);
